1. Messari: Stablecoin market value hits a new high of $258.5 billion, trading volume declines but fees surge;
2. Spiko, a tokenized money market fund platform, completes $22 million Series A financing, led by Index Ventures;
3. The Thai SEC and the Bank of Thailand have launched a sandbox program to allow foreign tourists to exchange digital assets for Thai baht;
4. Analysts: US tax cuts are expected to put pressure on the long end of US debt;
5. Speaker of the US House of Representatives: The ban on the Federal Reserve issuing digital currencies is planned to be included in the National Defense Authorization Act later this year;
6. Analysis: Trump's dismissal of Powell may cause the US dollar index to fall by 5%;
7. Binance: Users with Alpha points of no less than 213 can participate in this BAS pre-sale event;
8. CryptoQuant: Short-term holder MVRV shows that BTC still has room to rise;
9. Hong Kong-listed company Yili Holdings announced the issuance of convertible bonds worth HK$19.95 million to develop Web3 business.
